                                                        <h5 >Ensure correct
                                                            <code>role</code> and provide a label 
                                                            
                                                        </h5>
                                                        <p>An appropriate role attribute must be offered in order for assistive technology (like screen readers) to indicate that a group of buttons is present. This would be <code>role="group"</code> for button groups, and <code>role="toolbar"</code> for toolbars.
                                                        </p>
                                                        <p>
                                                        In addition, even when the right role property is present, groups and toolbars should have an explicit label because most assistive technologies won't otherwise announce them. While <code>aria-label</code> is used in the examples given here, there are other options available, such as <code>aria-labelledby</code>.
                                                        </p>
